legacy.full_text: My great pleasure to deliver remarks at the Netherlands - Hong Kong Friendship Dinner yesterday. We believe HK's future will only be brighter. And as I said in my remarks, int'l cooperation is more needed today than ever. China is part of the solution, not part of the problem. https://t.co/P9DZAT2oeS

I was interviewed by @ADnl. Under the leadership of the CPC, China has made great achievements. In the interview you’ll find some real stories of my family. I also answered questions on various issues. https://t.co/TkYYajAduV

legacy.full_text:
Would you like to try to make a #Zongzi, Chinese people’s favorite food for the #DragonBoatFestival? 

Here’s the exclusive instructional video by our chef👨‍🍳 ( and a mysterious challenger🤔). Watch it & try it! https://t.co/LyPnEmmaE9

I had a candid conversation with members of Dutch parliament. Dialogues based on mutual respect and equality are vital in dispeling disinformation and misunderstanding. I hope a more objective and just view could be formed on China.

Today I had the pleasure of meeting Mr. Jaap Smit @JaapSmitCdK, King's Commissioner of Zuid-Holland. We talked about the good local cooperation between our cities & provinces, and how to further promote it, which is very important for the Sino-Dutch relations. https://t.co/zCD8FsSEQD

The second part of CSP-25 of the CWC opened today. Read my intervention as the Head of the Chinese Delegation on the draft decision on Addressing the Possession and Use of Chemical Weapons by Syria. 
https://t.co/d7GNRaU49o https://t.co/Wjyd1rjtJn

value.string_value: By H.E. Mr. Jian Tan, Ambassador of the People’s Republic of China to the Kingdom of the Netherlands. It is a great honour as well as heavy responsibility for me to serve as ambassador of China to...
Enhancing Understanding and Strengthening Partnership - Diplomat magazine

legacy.full_text:
China and the Netherlands have shared interests and no fundamental interest conflict. As ambassador, I am committed to enhancing understanding and promoting partnership. 

Read my article published on DiplomatMagazine👉https://t.co/cnc6ztFRdN
The Ninety-Six Session of the Executive Council of the OPCW opened Today. Read my intervention as the Head of the Chinese Delegation under the General Debate. https://t.co/geyQP2wkN2

Today a great honor to present the Letter of Credentials appointed me as the Permanent Representative of China to the OPCW Director-General Ambassador Arias. 

I am ready to continue the good cooperation between China and the OPCW towards a world free of chemical weapons. https://t.co/BK1CGas0C0

A great honor to present the Letter of Credence today to His Majesty King Willem-Alexander @koninklijkhuis.

With confidence,  I will be committed to building stronger China - Netherlands relations. https://t.co/otTA7DGkYN

Honored to meet with Dutch Foreign Minister H.E. Mr. Blok @ministerBlok today. We had a great talk on the importance of 🇨🇳🇳🇱 relations. 

Looking forward to working with the Dutch side to further strengthen our open & pragmatic partnership for comprehensive cooperation.

legacy.full_text: Welcome to the #Netherlands, Ambassador Tan! On behalf of Ambassador @wjpgeerts, we wish you an auspicious stay, and we are looking forward to continuing our dialogue. https://t.co/1J6dR83F1p

Thank you Ambassador @wjpgeerts! Still in self-quarantine at my residence now, but already been deeply attracted by the beauty of 🇳🇱 and its culture. Looking forward to continuing our good talks and cooperation. 
Wish you and your team in Beijing a happy and prosperous new year!
